From: FIXME <FIXME>
Subject: [PATCH 4/5] media: i2c: ov5675: Reorder supply names for correct
 power sequencing

On TPS68470-based platforms the VSIO regulator controls the sensor-side
I2C bus.  Enabling VSIO (dovdd) before the sensor core supply (dvdd) can
cause I2C bus contention on the shared PMIC bus, leading to transaction
timeouts.

Reorder the supply array so that regulator_bulk_enable() powers the
rails in the order avdd -> dvdd -> dovdd, matching the sequencing
observed in the vendor (Windows) driver.  regulator_bulk_disable()
already tears down in reverse array order, which gives the correct
dovdd -> dvdd -> avdd power-off sequence.

On platforms where the three supplies come from independent regulators
the ordering has no effect.

Signed-off-by: FIXME <FIXME>
---
 drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c | 4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c
+++ b/drivers/media/i2c/ov5675.c
@@ -84,8 +84,8 @@ struct ov5675_mode {

 static const char * const ov5675_supply_names[] = {
 	"avdd",		/* Analog power */
-	"dovdd",	/* Digital I/O power */
 	"dvdd",		/* Digital core power */
+	"dovdd",	/* Digital I/O power */
 };

 #define OV5675_NUM_SUPPLIES	ARRAY_SIZE(ov5675_supply_names)
